A towering medieval castle with multiple concentric walls and gates, each layer progressively smaller toward the center, rendered in Studio Ghibli's soft watercolor animation style. The outermost wall is weathered stone with a heavy iron portcullis, the middle layers feature increasingly ornate architecture with glowing lanterns, and the innermost tower emanates a warm golden light from its windows. Tiny figures can be seen at various checkpoints along winding pathways between the walls. The scene is set at twilight with a gradient sky of peach and lavender, fluffy cumulus clouds drifting past. Moss and ivy grow on the lower walls while cherry blossom trees dot the courtyards between layers. The perspective is slightly elevated, showing the spiral path one must take through all defensive layers to reach the protected heart of the fortress.
